WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Hitokakera no yuuki hirogete
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:53.430
Saisho wa minna BARABARA ni egaite ita chiheisen

10
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

11
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

12
00:00:53.740 --> 00:01:00.440
Ima nara hitotsu no bouenkyou de nozokeru

13
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

14
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

15
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:09.980
Kimi no KOKORO madowasu unmei no shoppai KONPASU

16
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

17
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Sakate ni kaji toru yo
Set a new course, turn the tables now

18
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! SHIGARAMI mo kako mo sutete
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

19
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Bokura nara sore demo waraeteru hazu
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

20
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

21
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:34.900
Yume wo kanaeru tame no namida naraba

22
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

23
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
Oshiku wa nai PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

24
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
Mirai he no SHIPPO chotto mieta yo
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

25
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:56.050
Finale

26
00:01:53.340 --> 00:01:56.350
What? They rushed off the island?

27
00:01:56.350 --> 00:01:59.470
Yes. We couldn't even
give them our gift.

28
00:01:59.470 --> 00:02:01.810
What a pity...

29
00:02:02.980 --> 00:02:07.650
I wonder if they even realize
how grateful we are for what they did.

30
00:02:09.320 --> 00:02:13.110
Indeed. They still don't
grasp our feelings.

31
00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:18.410
It's not fair, Aisa...

32
00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:20.830
You're the only one who got
to say goodbye to them.

33
00:02:20.830 --> 00:02:24.670
They can't stop talking about
how we let our saviors run away.

34
00:02:25.880 --> 00:02:29.670
But Luffy and the others
told me not to tell anyone.

35
00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:34.630
Hey Raki, did you know that
Luffy's body stretches?!

36
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:37.800
He'd be like, "Gum-Gum Pistol!"

37
00:02:37.800 --> 00:02:40.430
Hey, Aisa, hold still!

38
00:02:40.430 --> 00:02:43.390
Who knew there was a strong
warrior in the Blue Sea, too?!

39
00:02:44.020 --> 00:02:48.060
I wanna be like him,
like "Gum-Gum...!"

40
00:02:49.610 --> 00:02:51.070
Aisa...

41
00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:56.030
Let's just give it a trim for today.
You should let your hair grow out.

42
00:02:56.030 --> 00:02:56.860
What?

43
00:02:56.860 --> 00:03:01.540
I'm sure it'll look good on you.
You're a girl, so you should look cute.

44
00:03:01.830 --> 00:03:06.170
Cute?! Me?!

45
00:03:07.670 --> 00:03:08.420
That's right!

46
00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:12.670
Now that there's no need
for you kids to carry weapons...

47
00:03:14.630 --> 00:03:19.100
you can live freely,
like people in the sky should.

48
00:03:21.140 --> 00:03:23.350
You sure are ladylike today!

49
00:03:24.520 --> 00:03:27.270
Now, hold still, Aisa!

50
00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:28.650
Ladylike Raki!

51
00:03:28.650 --> 00:03:29.900
Aisa!

52
00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:38.990
Great Warrior Kalgara...

53
00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:43.490
We were told that the sacred duty
of the Shandians had been fulfilled.

54
00:03:44.120 --> 00:03:47.710
And I'm sure your best friend
heard your wish as well.

55
00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:53.340
Future generations will no longer
need to shed their blood.

56
00:03:54.010 --> 00:03:59.010
Our fight may be over...
but we will never lose our pride!

57
00:03:59.590 --> 00:04:03.100
So please continue to watch over us.

58
00:04:05.310 --> 00:04:09.310
We swear to always keep
the Light of Shandora shining!

59
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:23.030
I am merely the Sky Knight,
a freelance mercenary.

60
00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:26.370
You are far better suited for it.

61
00:04:26.370 --> 00:04:29.670
This city belonged to your
people from the start.

62
00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:31.210
What's this now?

63
00:04:31.750 --> 00:04:34.130
That's not a good reason.

64
00:04:34.130 --> 00:04:36.960
I think this battle
taught us all the hard truth...

65
00:04:37.590 --> 00:04:40.640
that no one can claim
ownership of vearth.

66
00:04:40.970 --> 00:04:43.390
The title of "god" provides strength.

67
00:04:43.390 --> 00:04:47.100
The name of the land is Skypiea.
The name of the city is Shandora.

68
00:04:47.930 --> 00:04:50.020
The only person who
can unify them is you,

69
00:04:50.020 --> 00:04:55.610
the one who's always anguished over
this land's never-ending war.

70
00:04:57.070 --> 00:04:59.490
Sky Knight Gan Fall...

71
00:04:59.490 --> 00:05:01.570
I ask you to take the seat of god once more

72
00:05:01.570 --> 00:05:05.490
and give this ailing nation
the strength to heal.

73
00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:09.410
We'd like you to, as well!

74
00:05:09.410 --> 00:05:10.500
Lord Gan Fall!

75
00:05:10.830 --> 00:05:12.630
As long as it's you,
we're on board too!

76
00:05:12.630 --> 00:05:13.710
Yeah!

77
00:05:13.710 --> 00:05:15.040
Gan Fall!

78
00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:16.210
God!

79
00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:16.920
We need you!

80
00:05:20.680 --> 00:05:22.430
Alas...

81
00:05:23.550 --> 00:05:28.890
Just when I thought I could finally
grow pumpkins in peace...

82
00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:50.910
Lower Skypiea,
the White Sea

83
00:05:55.630 --> 00:05:57.210
Everyone! We can see it now!

84
00:05:58.380 --> 00:06:01.420
Take a look ahead! It's Cloud End!

85
00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:02.630
Ah! Lemme see!

86
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:06.930
Wow... So we can go
back down over there?

87
00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:09.100
We got here sooner than I thought.

88
00:06:11.270 --> 00:06:13.980
Do we have to leave already?

89
00:06:13.980 --> 00:06:17.690
Yeah, now that we're heading back,
I don't want to say goodbye.

90
00:06:17.690 --> 00:06:20.570
It's time to say farewell
to this pure white sea.

91
00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:23.740
The sky island was fun...
but it was scary, too.

92
00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:28.700
So there's a milky road through there that
heads straight down to the Blue Sea, huh?

93
00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:32.120
I wonder if we'll ever visit
the sky island again...

94
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.960
Maybe, maybe not.

95
00:06:42.920 --> 00:06:47.260
Well then, everyone! I'm sorry,
but we'll say goodbye here!

96
00:06:47.260 --> 00:06:49.060
Please take care, everyone!

97
00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.720
Thanks for seeing us off!

98
00:06:51.720 --> 00:06:54.390
Conis! Take care of yourself!

99
00:06:54.390 --> 00:06:56.350
Send our regards to the others, too!

100
00:06:56.900 --> 00:06:58.900
See you!

101
00:06:59.650 --> 00:07:01.690
Thanks for everything!

102
00:07:02.690 --> 00:07:07.160
No! We should be thanking you!

103
00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:10.990
I'll never forget you all!

104
00:07:11.490 --> 00:07:14.330
Conis, old guy, and fluff ball!
You all take care!

105
00:07:14.330 --> 00:07:15.500
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

106
00:07:15.500 --> 00:07:19.540
Now, furl the sails immediately
and hold on tight to the ship!

107
00:07:19.540 --> 00:07:21.670
Alright! Let's do as he says!

108
00:07:22.090 --> 00:07:23.970
Sounds like it's gonna go pretty fast!

109
00:07:23.970 --> 00:07:27.760
Yeah, we're sliding 7,000
meters down! Hurry!

110
00:07:27.760 --> 00:07:28.760
– Okay!
– Okay!

111
00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:35.020
Wh-What?! Huh?!

112
00:07:37.900 --> 00:07:40.060
He says, "Don't forget about me."

113
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:43.860
Oh... It's that south bird we
brought to the sky with us.

114
00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:48.530
Okay, Captain!

115
00:07:48.950 --> 00:07:51.160
We got the log for the next island!

116
00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:59.880
Alright! Once we get back down,
we'll start a brand new adventure!

117
00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:03.090
You ready, guys?!

118
00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:07.340
We're going back to the Blue Sea!

119
00:08:07.340 --> 00:08:08.760
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

120
00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:25.400
Everyone! Be careful while dropping!

121
00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:30.610
– Dropping?
– Dropping?

122
00:08:39.580 --> 00:08:41.000
Heso!

123
00:08:45.420 --> 00:08:50.050
Here we go! The sky island's
famous octoballoon!

124
00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:04.400
An octopus!

125
00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:06.280
You son of a...!

126
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:11.450
O-Ouch...

127
00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:14.410
Wh-Wh-What the...?!

128
00:09:16.370 --> 00:09:18.910
Hey, look! This is so cool!

129
00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:22.750
What the hell is this?!

130
00:09:22.750 --> 00:09:24.090
It's a balloon!

131
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:26.630
This is fun!

132
00:09:26.630 --> 00:09:27.710
We've slowed down!

133
00:09:27.710 --> 00:09:32.970
I... I thought that I was finally
gonna go to the netherworld.

134
00:10:00.250 --> 00:10:06.170
Ring it! Let the ringing of the bell bid
farewell to the saviors of this land!

135
00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:07.090
Heso!

136
00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:13.090
Luffy! Let's meet again!

137
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:14.800
Don't be a stranger!

138
00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:16.600
Thank you!

139
00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:20.430
Safe travels back to the Blue Sea!

140
00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:29.610
When you cast your gaze
toward the sky...

141
00:10:30.860 --> 00:10:34.660
Is it real, or is it but a dream,
this God Land above the clouds?

142
00:10:35.450 --> 00:10:37.450
Ten thousand meters high in the sky...

143
00:10:38.120 --> 00:10:41.040
If you listen closely, you can
hear the sound of a bell.

144
00:10:41.040 --> 00:10:43.960
It rings today. And it will
ring again tomorrow.

145
00:10:44.920 --> 00:10:47.290
The echoing sound
of the bell in the sky

146
00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:51.760
sings of the triumph of this
wandering land...

147
00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:02.430
This is cool!

148
00:11:02.430 --> 00:11:06.940
Yeah! This is great!

149
00:11:09.150 --> 00:11:10.980
You're calling off the search?!

150
00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:14.990
It's only natural, right?!
The City of Gold was in the sky.

151
00:11:14.990 --> 00:11:18.160
We won't find anything
at the bottom of the sea.

152
00:11:18.160 --> 00:11:20.160
This is the end.

153
00:11:20.160 --> 00:11:22.490
There's no point in staying here.

154
00:11:23.200 --> 00:11:24.080
Boss...

155
00:11:24.750 --> 00:11:26.170
Boss...

156
00:11:26.170 --> 00:11:33.840
I sincerely thank you all... for joining me
in pursuit of my dream all these years.

157
00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:35.300
What are you saying...?

158
00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:37.640
Don't treat us like strangers...

159
00:11:37.640 --> 00:11:38.970
Well then, gentlemen!

160
00:11:41.890 --> 00:11:44.850
What sort of romantic adventure
shall we go after next?!

161
00:11:50.900 --> 00:11:54.360
We'll follow you to the ends
of the world, boss!

162
00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:03.290
Gold! Gold! Gold! Gold! Gold!

163
00:12:03.790 --> 00:12:07.920
We're finally super rich!
What're we gonna buy?!

164
00:12:07.920 --> 00:12:11.250
What about a huge bronze statue?!

165
00:12:11.250 --> 00:12:14.590
You moron! Why would you
trade gold for bronze?!

166
00:12:14.590 --> 00:12:16.840
We should stock up on cannons!

167
00:12:16.840 --> 00:12:18.180
Let's buy ten of them! Ten!

168
00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:21.550
Nami! I want
a refrigerator with a lock!

169
00:12:21.550 --> 00:12:25.890
Don't be stupid! What're we gonna
do when we get hungry?! I object!

170
00:12:22.600 --> 00:12:25.470
I... I... I want you to
buy me some books!

171
00:12:25.470 --> 00:12:27.980
I wanna read medical
books from other countries!

172
00:12:25.890 --> 00:12:27.980
That's why we should
buy it, dumbass!

173
00:12:27.980 --> 00:12:30.060
Now hold on just a second, you guys!

174
00:12:30.730 --> 00:12:34.230
We'll split the treasure once
we get back down, okay?

175
00:12:34.230 --> 00:12:35.900
Please buy books for me!

176
00:12:36.570 --> 00:12:40.530
If we spend our money willy-nilly,
we'll end up wasting it all.

177
00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:52.000
The sun's completely set now.

178
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.590
It's a nice view, though.

179
00:12:53.590 --> 00:12:56.300
Yeah, you're right.

180
00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:11.600
It's freezing...!

181
00:13:11.600 --> 00:13:13.900
Nami! Robin! Are you okay?

182
00:13:17.070 --> 00:13:18.440
That startled me!

183
00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:21.160
The octopus suddenly
shrank all the way!

184
00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:22.820
Maybe it was an air leak.

185
00:13:22.820 --> 00:13:24.490
What the heck happened?!

186
00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:30.330
Well, we somehow made
it down... without dying.

187
00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:32.040
Thanks a bunch!

188
00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:33.830
Still...

189
00:13:38.880 --> 00:13:41.380
we really went to an
incredible place, didn't we?

190
00:13:41.380 --> 00:13:44.430
Now that we're down here,
it seems so far away.

191
00:13:44.430 --> 00:13:46.470
It's like we were dreaming.

192
00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:49.980
It's a dream land. I wonder
if we can go visit again some day.

193
00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:52.690
You might be able to
get closer if you die.

194
00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:55.860
Zoro, do you really think
you'll be allowed into heaven?

195
00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:57.610
Shut it!

196
00:13:57.610 --> 00:14:00.280
At any rate, things have calmed down.

197
00:14:00.280 --> 00:14:01.860
I'll make coffee or something.

198
00:14:01.860 --> 00:14:03.990
Better yet, make us
some dinner, Sanji!

199
00:14:03.990 --> 00:14:07.370
Yeah, yeah, I'll get right on it.
Just sit tight and have some coffee.

200
00:14:10.790 --> 00:14:13.290
It's pirate loot,
so we'll divide it equally!

201
00:14:14.380 --> 00:14:16.000
We each get some?!

202
00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:16.920
Naturally.

203
00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:18.380
I've been waiting for this!

204
00:14:18.380 --> 00:14:21.010
I'm gonna buy a bronze statue!

205
00:14:21.010 --> 00:14:22.930
Yeah! Can I buy books?!

206
00:14:23.550 --> 00:14:28.060
New pots, frying pans, silverware,
and giant mousetraps...

207
00:14:28.060 --> 00:14:30.560
That leaves a crapload left over!

208
00:14:30.560 --> 00:14:32.390
I could drink all I want!

209
00:14:32.730 --> 00:14:35.350
First, 80 percent goes to my stash!

210
00:14:35.940 --> 00:14:37.150
– Hold on a second!
– Hold on a second!

211
00:14:37.150 --> 00:14:39.070
Just kidding.

212
00:14:39.070 --> 00:14:43.110
Obviously! You can't have
a public secret stash!

213
00:14:43.110 --> 00:14:49.080
By "stash," I mean our
repair fund for the ship!

214
00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:52.120
The ship? You mean Merry?

215
00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:56.290
That's right. The Going Merry is
what brought us all this way.

216
00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:57.840
Come to think of it,

217
00:14:57.840 --> 00:15:04.010
she's been our ride across the seas
ever since my village in the East Blue...

218
00:15:04.010 --> 00:15:07.430
She's done so much for us,
but now she's all beat up.

219
00:15:07.430 --> 00:15:10.890
Good idea! The Great Repair
of the Going Merry!

220
00:15:10.890 --> 00:15:12.680
I'm all for it!

221
00:15:12.680 --> 00:15:14.230
Alright, dig in.

222
00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:19.360
Yeah, come to think of it, Usopp's
cheap repairs are just about at their limit.

223
00:15:19.360 --> 00:15:22.070
Hey, I'm just a marksman, you know!

224
00:15:22.070 --> 00:15:28.660
Yeah. We should go to a real shipyard
and have real shipwrights fix it for us.

225
00:15:29.950 --> 00:15:32.410
People can fix ships
better than Usopp?

226
00:15:32.660 --> 00:15:35.040
We have to fix her up properly
from time to time,

227
00:15:35.040 --> 00:15:36.670
or we'll pay for it later!

228
00:15:36.670 --> 00:15:38.000
Alright, it's decided!

229
00:15:38.580 --> 00:15:40.710
Let's add a shipwright to our crew!

230
00:15:41.590 --> 00:15:43.880
We still have a long way to go!

231
00:15:43.880 --> 00:15:45.170
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

232
00:15:45.170 --> 00:15:47.470
We need someone
with those skills anyway.

233
00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:49.930
Merry is our home!

234
00:15:50.350 --> 00:15:51.390
Our life!

235
00:15:51.970 --> 00:15:55.270
Let's find a shipwright
who can keep her safe!

236
00:15:57.900 --> 00:15:59.270
There he goes again...

237
00:15:59.270 --> 00:16:03.280
Yeah, on rare occasion,
he really hits the nail on the head.

238
00:16:03.280 --> 00:16:06.070
That'd be perfect! Let's do it!

239
00:16:06.650 --> 00:16:08.030
Okay, then that's the plan!

240
00:16:08.030 --> 00:16:10.530
I hope we find someone good!

241
00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:12.030
And we need a musician, too!

242
00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:13.490
No, we really don't.

243
00:16:20.040 --> 00:16:22.340
What's all the ruckus?!

244
00:16:22.340 --> 00:16:23.710
Run!

245
00:16:24.340 --> 00:16:27.050
Quit pushing! W-We gotta
stay away from 'em!

246
00:16:27.050 --> 00:16:28.010
A falling out?!

247
00:16:41.190 --> 00:16:42.310
Bellamy!

248
00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:43.690
Sarquiss!

249
00:16:43.690 --> 00:16:45.440
Please! Make him stop!

250
00:16:46.150 --> 00:16:51.240
Please! Just stop it!
Why are you doing this...?!

251
00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:53.160
What's happening?!

252
00:16:53.160 --> 00:16:55.330
Sarquiss is the one begging to stop?

253
00:16:55.330 --> 00:16:59.040
Why? Why, you ask?

254
00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:02.130
Sarquiss... Bellamy...

255
00:17:03.790 --> 00:17:07.760
It's because you disrespected
my flag, of course.

256
00:17:10.840 --> 00:17:13.720
"Does the sky island exist or not?"

257
00:17:14.100 --> 00:17:17.560
"Is the City of Gold real or not?"

258
00:17:19.690 --> 00:17:22.440
I couldn't care less about any of that.

259
00:17:23.110 --> 00:17:26.400
"Pit belief against belief
to gain control over others."

260
00:17:27.190 --> 00:17:28.820
That's what I told you...

261
00:17:28.820 --> 00:17:30.860
wasn't it, Bellamy?

262
00:17:32.160 --> 00:17:35.450
That's... Donquixote Doflamingo!

263
00:17:35.450 --> 00:17:38.080
He's one of the Seven
Warlords of the Sea!

264
00:17:38.080 --> 00:17:40.710
His bounty used to be
over 300 million!

265
00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:42.750
What's a guy like him doing here?!

266
00:17:42.750 --> 00:17:47.880
I don't need useless punks
like you serving under me...

267
00:17:48.630 --> 00:17:51.050
Crap! My body's moving on its own!

268
00:17:51.050 --> 00:17:54.090
Stop! Please, don't...!

269
00:17:54.510 --> 00:17:56.930
No!

270
00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:01.600
Bellamy!

271
00:18:05.270 --> 00:18:08.110
G-Give me...

272
00:18:08.860 --> 00:18:11.990
Give me one more chance...!

273
00:18:12.650 --> 00:18:16.620
I'll... We'll be your loyal followers!

274
00:18:16.620 --> 00:18:17.830
Bellamy!

275
00:18:17.830 --> 00:18:19.450
No more, Bellamy!

276
00:18:21.620 --> 00:18:25.580
Yes, I lost, but I never went
against your principles!

277
00:18:25.580 --> 00:18:27.210
I swear on your flag!

278
00:18:27.210 --> 00:18:29.880
This is just my way of doing things!

279
00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:32.420
We couldn't just run him off!

280
00:18:32.420 --> 00:18:35.590
He would've reached you someday!

281
00:18:36.800 --> 00:18:40.140
How very touching,
O faithful subordinate of mine.

282
00:18:40.470 --> 00:18:45.020
That's what I like about you, Bellamy.

283
00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:51.940
A new era is just around
the corner. Do as you wish.

284
00:18:53.240 --> 00:18:56.530
However... I don't need you anymore.

285
00:18:59.410 --> 00:19:02.330
Doflamingo!

286
00:19:08.130 --> 00:19:11.550
He just took out a notorious rookie
worth 55 million!

287
00:19:11.550 --> 00:19:13.300
It was child's play to him!

288
00:19:15.010 --> 00:19:16.890
It's finally beginning!

289
00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:19.300
You'd better be prepared!

290
00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:23.180
A world where only true pirates
can survive is drawing near!

291
00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:25.560
The powerless among you—
run while you can!

292
00:19:25.560 --> 00:19:27.560
With the inevitable tides of time,

293
00:19:27.560 --> 00:19:31.070
a new era of champions
will soon be upon us!

